a HTTP/HTTPS daemon

 HTTPd features:
 - User-Certificate signin
 - uploads on PUT and POST with LDP-Container interface
 - paging containers (aka directories/folders)
    summarization, Link headers, sorted-ranges, offsets/cursors
 - lazy indexing via GET (linked to traversible container)
 - follows http://linkeddata.github.io/SoLiD/ guidelines

 MIME-types
 input: RDF.rb formats + Atom/RSS, email, chat, text, CSV, Markdown, code
 output: RDF.rb formats + Atom/RSS, HTML (classic), HTML5+JS data-browsers

SRC git@gitlab.com:ix/pw.git https://github.com/hallwaykid/pw http://repo.or.cz/w/www.git

PRE-INSTALL

# void
$ xbps-install base-devel ruby ruby-devel libgit2-devel libxml2-devel libxslt-devel source-highlight python-Pygments
$ gem install bundler

# debian
$ apt-get install ruby bundler libssl-dev libgit2-dev libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev pkg-config

INSTALL
$ cd ruby
$ ruby install   # link source to ruby $sitelibdir
$ bundle install # fetch ruby libraries

USE
$ cd ..
$ cp conf/daemon/Procfile . # select Rack-engine
$ foreman start             # start HTTP/HTTPS-daemons

listen on 80/443: setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep $(realpath `which ruby`)
           >1024: run behind apache/nginx/lighttpd, see conf/

repl$ irb -rww

CLEAN
$ rm -rf cache index
